						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up by the side of the cart track to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Veṅkaṭapati.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1517, Manmatha, Kārttīka, śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1595 A.D., November 7, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record gifts of lands made to the artisans etc. The names of the donor and the donee are lost. It also refers to Nandēla Aubhaḷarāju.</p>						

						</summary>
